    <h3>Nancy K. Marder, O.T.R./C.H.T.</h3>
    <p>
      Nancy K. Marder, OTR/CHT graduated from SUNY Buffalo with a BS in Occupational
      Therapy and then received an Advanced Masters in Occupational Therapy from New
      York University. She has been practicing occupational therapy for over 30 years. She
      began her career at DC General Hospital and at Bellevue Hospital as a Staff OT. She
      then worked at The New York Hospital, heading up the Hand Therapy Rehabilitation
      Program. She became a Board Certified Hand Therapist in 1991.
    </p>
    <p>
      In 1989, Nancy opened up her private practice, South Shore Hand Therapy and
      Occupational Therapy PLLC. She is highly skilled in custom splint fabrication and
      treatment of a variety of diagnoses including tendon repair, nerve injury, tendonitis, and
      fractures. She enjoys helping people with simple to complex upper extremity problems
      to decrease pain and regain motion, strength and function. Nancy will work closely with
      you and your physician to help you achieve the best functional result possible. Nancy
      also works with children who have undergone reconstructive surgery for cerebral palsy
      and congenital differences.
    </p>
